# 7. みんなの居場所に

MEIKO: Where am I...?
MEIKO: Did everyone's feelings help create this cafe...?
MEIKO: But no one else seems to be here.
MEIKO: In that case...
MEIKO: There's an assortment of coffee beans and tea leaves here. And the refrigerator appears to be full of cooking ingredients...
MEIKO: For now, I think I'll brew myself a cup...
MEIKO: (She's this SEKAI's version of me...)
MEIKO: (But this cafe seems completely empty... Is this the moment just after this SEKAI was created?)
MEIKO: Okay, the beans are all ground up.
MEIKO: Oh, what a lovely aroma... I'm sure this coffee is going to taste wonderful.
MEIKO: (I sensed a powerful desire while walking through those alleyways just now...)
MEIKO: (The desire to surpass RAD WEEKEND.)
MEIKO: RAD WEEKEND... The flyers I saw must've been for that...
MEIKO: I don't know what kind of event it actually was, but I'm sure it was something spectacular...
MEIKO: The owners of these feelings... An and the others... They're probably singing and practicing right now in order to accomplish that goal.
MEIKO: (I wonder what they're like...)
MEIKO: Hehe. For one, I'm sure they all love to sing, and are very passionate about what they do.
MEIKO: Does that also mean this cafe has a special place in their hearts?
MEIKO: If so, I'll need to handle this place with great care...
MEIKO: I guess this SEKAI's version of me has always been a skilled barista...
MEIKO: Hehe. It really is a lovely aroma.
Miku: Oh, MEIKO... Did you just brew up some coffee?
MEIKO: Yes, I did. Would you like a cup as well, Miku?
Miku: I'd love one.
MEIKO: Just give me one second. Okay, here you are.
Miku: Thank you.
Miku: Mmm... This is delicious.
Miku: You could probably start your own cafe if you're this good at brewing coffee, MEIKO.
MEIKO: Oh, you think so?
Miku: Yes, and this place just happens to be vacant, so why not give it a go?
Miku: Especially since this place was probably made with them in mind...
MEIKO: Right...
MEIKO: I thought the same thing.
MEIKO: I also have a feeling that this cafe is going to be important to them.
MEIKO: So...
MEIKO: I want this cafe to be a place where they can relax.
MEIKO: Since the place they're aiming for is so high up.
MEIKO: I want to provide an oasis where they can go when they're feeling tired after practice, having a tough time or worrying about something.
MEIKO: I want this cafe to be that kind of place.
Miku: And I'm sure it will be... After all, MEIKO, you're a great listener.
Miku: And you make great coffee.
MEIKO: Hehe. If you're willing to give me your seal of approval, Miku, then I guess I don't have anything to worry about.
Miku: Well, I am pretty picky about these things.
Miku: Still, I'm looking forward to everyone coming to visit this cafe for the first time.
MEIKO: Yes, so am I... Before they do, I'll need to come up with a menu that they'll really enjoy.
MEIKO: Starting with... Maybe my own original blend?
Miku: Oh, I'll be looking forward to the way that turns out.
MEIKO: All this just for them...
MEIKO: She seems like such a reliable person...
MEIKO: And you're right. This cafe is going to have a very special place in their hearts.
MEIKO: So, please help them out for me... Me...
Miku: Oh, MEIKO, if you're going to run a cafe, then I think you'll want to have some food on the menu and not just coffee.
MEIKO: Yes, you're right... They're bound to get hungry after their practices.
MEIKO: But I'm not sure about how everything is going to taste.
Miku: I say just give it a try. I'll be here to taste test everything.
MEIKO: Oh? Is that another way of saying that you're hungry, Miku?
